# shadcn/ui Usage — MANDATORY

This project uses [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) as the **one and only** UI component library. **No custom UI components, primitives, or hand-rolled styles are permitted under any circumstances.**

## Absolute Rules

- **NEVER** create custom UI components (buttons, inputs, modals, cards, badges, etc.) from scratch.
- **NEVER** use any third-party UI library other than shadcn/ui (no MUI, Chakra, Radix directly, Headless UI, etc.).
- **NEVER** build a UI element by hand if a shadcn/ui component exists for it — even for "simple" things like a button or a divider.
- **ALWAYS** install the shadcn/ui component via CLI if it is not yet in `components/ui/`.
- **ALL** Clerk sign-in and sign-up trigger buttons must use the shadcn/ui `<Button>` component — never Clerk's built-in `<SignInButton>` or `<SignUpButton>` default rendering.
- **ALL** Clerk authentication flows (sign-in, sign-up) must open in a **modal** — never redirect to a separate page. Use `mode="modal"` on `<SignInButton>` and `<SignUpButton>`.

## Initialization

If shadcn/ui is not yet set up in the project:

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest init -t next
```

## Adding Components

Install components on demand. Example for the `button` component:

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the desired component name (e.g. `card`, `dialog`, `input`, `table`, etc.).

## Clerk Auth Buttons — Required Pattern

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — shadcn Button wrapping Clerk, modal mode
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from "@clerk/nextjs";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

<SignUpButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign Up</Button>
</SignUpButton>

// ❌ WRONG — Clerk default button (not shadcn/ui)
<SignInButton />

// ❌ WRONG — redirects instead of modal
<SignInButton mode="redirect">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

// ❌ WRONG — custom styled button
<button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2">Sign In</button>
```

## Rules Summary

- Check `components/ui/` before building any UI element — it may already be installed.
- If a needed component is not in `components/ui/`, add it via the CLI above; never build it manually.
- Import components from `@/components/ui/<component>`, not from third-party libraries.
- Zero exceptions: every visible UI element must trace back to a shadcn/ui component.
